{"word":"μορφόω","slug":"μορφόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>μορφόω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μορφή\">μορφή</a></el>] ‘cause a condition in which an entity become perceptible’, <b>to shape/form,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pass.\">pass.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on distinctive characteristics <el>μέχρις <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:οὗ\">οὗ</a> μορφωϑῇ Χριστὸς <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐν\">ἐν</a> ὑμῖν</el> until Christ takes shape in you <b><a href='B:550 4:19'>Gal 4:19</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:μορφή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:μόρφωσις\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}